Dear Red Rock Elementary Families,

On September 14, Red Rock Elementary will begin our ‚Äúphased‚Äù reopening . Our ‚Äúphased‚Äù reopening will be as followed:

- Monday, September 14, Kindergarten through 2nd grade will be welcomed back on campus.

- Tuesday, September 15, Kindergarten through 5th will be welcomed back on campus.

- Wednesday, September 16, Kindergarten through 8th will be welcomed back on campus.

Our hope with ‚Äúphased‚Äù reopening will allow our younger grade levels an opportunity to adapt to our new changes in daily routines.

Your input on how we move forward together as a community is extremely important to us. We have attached a survey that will provide us with very valuable information as we transition into our ‚Äúhybrid‚Äù model. We ask that you please take a moment to fill out this survey. https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSfOqoACkKebO4jKLZeHH87M_rgKe5mO_Wwa31e-i8BHBGw3sQ/viewform

If you have already filled out the survey, thank you. If you have not had a chance, we would truly appreciate your time to fill it out.

Respectfully,

Peter Dwyer

District Administrator

post_text:
Dear Red Rock Families,

We are happy to announce that Santa Cruz Valley Union High School will be serving FREE meals for our community starting June 2nd. Santa Cruz will be serving food pre bagged with breakfast and lunch just as we did during the school year. These meals are available to those that are 18 years and younger. The meals may be picked up by an adult or child. The food will be distributed from the back of the cafeteria, just as before. There are a couple differences from before, the food service will begin on Tuesday June 2nd from 9:00AM through 10:00AM. Food service will be Tuesday through Thursday from 9:00AM-10:00AM through the summer.

This is a FREE service provided by Santa Cruz Valley Union High School. We are very thankful for their support within our community.

If you have any questions please contact the office during summer hours.

Thank you,
Peter Dwyer
District Administrator

Our 8th Grade Video Promotion is complete and has been sent to our 8th grade families via email. We are so happy with how it came together! We will not be releasing the full video on social media, as we will honor the privacy of our families who elected not to release their child to our school social media. We will, however, share our speeches from our District Administrator Mr. Dwyer, as well as our student speakers who gave fantastic speeches.

Thank you so much for helping make this a memorable promotion experience for our 8th graders. We have enjoyed putting together this promotion video and our parade. 8th grade families: please make sure you received the link for the promotion video, and the kids received their bag with their report card, promotion certificate, promotion picture if taken, t-shirt, summer book packs, and the Defy gift card. Please reach out to us if you have any questions.

SCHOOL CLOSURE UPDATE

On Friday, March 20, 2020, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman announced a two-week extension of school closures through Friday, April 10, 2020. Going forward, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman will continue to provide updates and guidance about the need for continued school closures beyond that date.

They will continue to work together and assess this situation on a 24/7 basis. During this time, the Arizona Department of Education will continue to develop and share guidance to schools regarding instructional time, statewide testing, provision of special education services, school meals, and more.

https://azgovernor.gov/governor/blog/2020/03/open-letter-arizona-families-educators-school-leaders-and-education-march-20-2020
text:
SCHOOL CLOSURE UPDATE

On Friday, March 20, 2020, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman announced a two-week extension of school closures through Friday, April 10, 2020. Going forward, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman will continue to provide updates and guidance about the need for continued school closures beyond that date.

They will continue to work together and assess this situation on a 24/7 basis. During this time, the Arizona Department of Education will continue to develop and share guidance to schools regarding instructional time, statewide testing, provision of special education services, school meals, and more.

post_text: Over Winter Break our basketball team will be collecting pledges for our Free-A-Thon to be completed in January. Each player will shoot 100 free throws, and each made free throw will result in $$$, depending on how much money the pledge is. For example, a pledge of $0.50 for 60 free throws made would be a $30 donation. The money collected will go directly towards our athletics program, such as league fees, and upgrades equipment/jerseys. Flat donations are also welcome! Thank you for your support.

post_text:
Dear Families,

Today we were informed by Department of Public Safety, to go into a soft lockdown due to an incident that happened nearby in Red Rock Village this morning around 10:45 a.m. The person of concern was in custody, but as a precautionary, we went into a lockdown at the request of DPS. All students were safe and continued with classroom instruction as usual. The soft lockdown was only for 5 minutes before DPS informed us it was safe to lift the lockdown. If you have any questions, please contact the office.

Respectfully,
Peter Dwyer
Principal

post_text:
Dear Families,

In an effort to provide a safe and secure learning environment at our school, we would like to inform you that Red Rock Elementary will be performing a planned lock down practice drill on Thursday, November 14 at 9:00 AM.

School administration, with the support of Pinal County Sheriff's Office and Avra Valley Fire Department, are conducting these drills to practice our Emergency Response procedures. The drills are to ensure that students and staff are aware of our outlined procedures, including, where to report, what to do, and how to respond as a school.

These drills also help us to understand where our gaps in protocols are so they may be addressed and improved upon.

We encourage you to talk with your children and discuss with them what their classroom protocols are and see if they have any questions that we can help them with. Please feel free to contact the school with any of your questions.

Respectfully,
Peter Dwyer,
Principal

post_text: Today we are honored to have this flag presented to Red Rock Elementary. This particular flag was flown over the capitol building in Washington D.C. just for Red Rock Elementary. We would like to thank our Governing Board Member JoAnna Mendoza for arranging this for us. This flag along with a commemorative certificate will be displayed in the office for all of us to see. The flag symbolizes for us the sacrifices that our active military, our veterans, and their families have made and continue to make for us.
